replies.body:
Hey I Play League79!

I completely understand your frustration.  While these errors appear to be a result of unintentional tech issues, LeaverBuster cannot determine the difference between intentional or unintentional problems (such as someone unplugging their router instead of having an internet outage, or someone uninstalling their drivers mid-game to force a crash as opposed to a legitimate crash).  In addition to this, even though you didn't intend to leave, the other 4 players on your team had an unfair 4v5 battle.  The initial warning and subsequent penalties are meant to notify you that leaving is not ok, and that you should work to resolve the issues first, before jumping into another game with other players.  Playing a Custom Game with just bots is a good way to test to see if your still having issues or resolved them!;

Also, I'm very glad to hear that you seem to have found the fix to your game freezing.  Certain 3rd party programs that run in the background have been known to negatively affect League of Legends, and might be a good idea to disable them before playing.  While we can't alter LeaverBuster, if you continue to experience issues, we'd be glad to help in resolving it completely! :)
